<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-01-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="997" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d997">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Lee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Havana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-01-27"><hi rend="italic">January 27,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Just visited General Parrado, Acting Governor-General, with Sigsbee and
                            two of his officers. We were most cordially received, and Parrado
                            returns visit by going aboard <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi>
                            to-morrow.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>